{"id": "EUVD-2022-54484", "enisaUuid": "f3c7f3fe-c12a-3ce5-bfee-0c5370b30dbe", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/bridge: Add missing pm_runtime_put_sync\n\npm_runtime_get_sync() will increase the rumtime PM counter\neven when it returns an error. Thus a pairing decrement is needed\nto prevent refcount leak. Fix this by replacing this API with\npm_runtime_resume_and_get(), which will not change the runtime\nPM counter on error. Besides, a matching decrement is needed\non the error handling path to keep the counter balanced.", "datePublished": "2025-02-26T01:55:05", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:57:03", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ff13c90d7f7ab606b37be6d15140d19013d6736c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/792533e54cd6e89191798ccd1abd590c62b9077e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9df80dc738926a2ea4bd1ce5993c3d0f4b0e855c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/46f47807738441e354873546dde0b000106c068a"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49128"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "025d8058-542d-3959-b00b-b9d7d8d1a23b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.8"}, {"id": "0ea42681-db57-3a01-8ef9-78782557138a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.34"}, {"id": "548e8a45-1ed0-363f-be89-cd628316ecec", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "68cae6b8-9db8-360a-96b4-be71644de98b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "44cfc6233447cb2cf47aeb99457de35826a363f6 <ff13c90d7f7ab606b37be6d15140d19013d6736c"}, {"id": "8adf3b7d-c97a-3832-8d00-b1737f22b8ed", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18"}, {"id": "93540b19-ab5f-3599-8abd-b7e4aa87f279", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "44cfc6233447cb2cf47aeb99457de35826a363f6 <9df80dc738926a2ea4bd1ce5993c3d0f4b0e855c"}, {"id": "9a6